    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-16T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-16T21:00:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/1793: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-16T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 16, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>543. My number 538 of December 15, 7 p.m. Notes exchanged today. Ecuador accepts
                    all measures proposed in Department’s telegram number 387 of December 13, 8
                        p.m.<note n="33" xml:id="d212fn33">See footnote 29, <ref target="#pg_268">p.
                            268</ref>.</note> Copies of notes follow via next air mail.<note n="34"
                        xml:id="d212fn34">For text of U.S. note, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
